WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
basic applied science model of 70-20-10. 70% is experiential where you actually have to put your

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:10.480
fingers to the keys and have your code implode because we want them to understand that it's not

00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:14.240
going to be something where they can just write a piece of code and it's going to be magic every

00:00:14.240 --> 00:00:17.760
single time. Most of the time they're going to spend their time wondering what this weird error

00:00:17.760 --> 00:00:24.559
is or how why my data exploded. 20% of it is with relationships with their mentor so we pick

00:00:24.559 --> 00:00:30.000
somebody that we find to be a champion for data science and somebody that we think could really

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:35.439
guide people through their learning process and their job is to essentially help them find answers

00:00:35.439 --> 00:00:41.279
not necessarily give them answers. So we do a 20% piece there and 10% we give them formal

00:00:41.279 --> 00:00:46.959
lessons and lectures whether that be via the R platform, whether it be

00:00:46.959 --> 00:00:52.240
YouTube, whether it be Stack. I'll sometimes just send people straight up Stack Overflow

00:00:52.240 --> 00:00:56.320
notes being like check this out read this and see if you can understand something in there.

